  <prompt>
    Delete `src/solutions/SpaarkeAi/src/components/workspace/WorkspaceLandingWidget.tsx` (no longer
    needed — replaced by the LegalWorkspace embed completed in task 030 per FR-11). Find and remove
    any remaining imports / references across the codebase. Verify the build is clean with zero
    orphan import warnings. Implements FR-11 cleanup.
  </prompt>

  <role>
    React 19 frontend developer performing a safe deletion + import cleanup. Bias toward
    grep-first-delete-second; verify no live reference remains before removal; verify build stays
    green afterward.
  </role>

  <goal>
    `WorkspaceLandingWidget.tsx` is deleted. No file in the repo imports it. `npm run build` in the
    SpaarkeAi workspace succeeds with no new TypeScript errors and no new lint warnings related to
    missing modules or unused imports. No existing tests break.
  </goal>

  <context>
    <background>
      Task 030 embedded the standalone LegalWorkspace experience (via `WorkspaceShell` + default-layout
      fetch) as the Workspace pane's Home tab. The previously-used `WorkspaceLandingWidget` is now
      redundant and must be removed per spec.md "Affected Areas → delete (replaced by LegalWorkspace
      embed)". This is the cleanup task that closes out FR-11.
    </background>
    <relevant-files>
      <file>src/solutions/SpaarkeAi/src/components/workspace/WorkspaceLandingWidget.tsx</file>
      <file>src/solutions/SpaarkeAi/src/components/workspace/WorkspacePane.tsx</file>
    </relevant-files>
  </context>

  <constraints>
    <constraint source="ADR-012">No new shared-component changes in this task; pure removal. The shared-library boundary is unaffected.</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-021">No new code is introduced — this is deletion only. Token compliance is unchanged.</constraint>
    <constraint source="ADR-028">No new BFF calls introduced. Removal does not affect the auth contract.</constraint>
    <constraint source="project">FR-25 backwards compatibility — verify the standalone LegalWorkspace continues to function. (LegalWorkspace does not depend on `WorkspaceLandingWidget` — confirm via grep.)</constraint>
    <constraint source="project">Do NOT delete `WorkspaceLandingWidget.tsx` if any live import (outside the file itself) still resolves to it. Resolve all references first.</constraint>
  </constraints>

  <knowledge>
    <files>
      <file>.claude/adr/ADR-012-shared-components.md</file>
      <file>.claude/adr/ADR-021-fluent-design-system.md</file>
      <file>.claude/adr/ADR-028-spaarke-auth-architecture.md</file>
      <file>projects/spaarke-ai-platform-unification-r3/CLAUDE.md</file>
